Location fo PDFs not set. To use this workflow with PDF Expert, you need to set the location of your PDFs with "aconf".

export PATH=/usr/local/bin:$PATH
file_path="{query}"
doi="no DOI" hasDoiURL=`pdfgrep --count --ignore-case --page-range=1-3 --regexp='https?://[[:graph:]]*doi.org[[:graph:]]*' $file_path` if [[ $hasDoiURL > 0 ]] then doi=`pdfgrep --only-matching --ignore-case --page-range=1-3 --regexp="https?://[[:graph:]]*doi.org[[:graph:]]*" $file_path | head -n 1` fi
hasDOI=`pdfgrep --count --ignore-case --page-range=1-3 --regexp='DOI: ?[[:graph:]]*' $file_path` if [[ $hasDOI > 0 ]] then doiNumber=`pdfgrep --only-match --ignore-case --page-range=1-3 --regexp="DOI: *[[:graph:]]*" $file_path | head -n 1` doi=`sed -E 's/doi: */https:\/\/doi.org\//gi' <<< $doiNumber` fi
if [[ $doi == "no DOI" ]] then echo -n "no DOI" else echo -n $doi fi
tell application "Finder" to set sel to selection if ((count sel) > 1) then set firstItem to item 1 of sel return POSIX path of (firstItem as text) else return POSIX path of (sel as text) end if

[{"title":"📚 Open Library","arg":"open","subtitle":"in default text editor"},{"title":"🧼 Clean Library","arg":"clean","subtitle":"creates a backup before doing so"},{"imagefile":"75f622db7da6395893e172b6ebf9c5cce07bc698.png","title":"❇️ Create Library Backup","arg":"backup","subtitle":""}]

# resolve "~" library_path="~/Google Drive/BibDesk/My Library.bib"
# determine locations resolved_library_path=~`echo -n $library_path | sed -e "s/~//"` file_name="${resolved_library_path##*/}" parent_folder="${resolved_library_path%/*.*}" timestamp=`date '+%Y-%m-%d_%H.%M'` bkp_file="$parent_folder/Library Backups/${timestamp}_$file_name"
# create backups mkdir $parent_folder"/Library Backups/" cp $resolved_library_path $bkp_file
# delete when there are too many backups actual_number=$((number_of_bkps_to_save + 1)) cd $parent_folder"/Library Backups/" ls -t | tail -n +$actual_number | tr '\n' '\0' | xargs -0 rm
# echos for the notification echo -n $file_name

export PATH=/usr/local/bin:$PATH
doi="no DOI" hasDoiURL=`pdfgrep --count --ignore-case --page-range=1-3 --regexp='https?://[[:graph:]]*doi.org[[:graph:]]*' $file_path` if [[ $hasDoiURL > 0 ]] then doi=`pdfgrep --only-matching --ignore-case --page-range=1-3 --regexp="https?://[[:graph:]]*doi.org[[:graph:]]*" $file_path | head -n 1` fi
hasDOI=`pdfgrep --count --ignore-case --page-range=1-3 --regexp='DOI: ?[[:graph:]]*' $file_path` if [[ $hasDOI > 0 ]] then doiNumber=`pdfgrep --only-match --ignore-case --page-range=1-3 --regexp="DOI: *[[:graph:]]*" $file_path | head -n 1` doi=`sed -E 's/doi: */https:\/\/doi.org\//gi' <<< $doiNumber` fi
if [[ $doi == "no DOI" ]] then echo -n "no DOI" else curl --silent -LH "Accept: text/x-bibliography; style=$citation_style; locale=$lang" $doi fi

Requirements - [pdfgrep](https://gitlab.com/pdfgrep/pdfgrep) to be able to extract bibliographies from PDF Expert or Preview. - [BibItNow!](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/bibitnow/bmnfikjlonhkoojjfddnlbinkkapmldg)
- recommended autorenaming pattern for usage with the [PDF Annotation Extractor](https://github.com/chrisgrieser/pdf-annotation-extractor-alfred): `%p11/%p[ ][ et al]2/%p[_][_et al]2_%Y%u0_%t60%s{Pages}[_][]%w{Pages}[--][/][-]2`
- The `second_backup_dest` can be used for shared folder or to save an additional copy in the iCloud for the iOS BibTeX Viewer [References](https://apps.apple.com/de/app/references/id1481843213)
